article.headline: Murray State 66, Eastern Illinois 65
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Darnell Hopkins went 8-of-8 from the field, including 6-of-6 from 3-point range, to score 23 points Monday and lead Murray State to a 66-65 victory over Eastern Illinois. Murray (9-4, 6-1 Ohio Valley Conference) led 40-30 at halftime but shot only 11-of-28 (39.3 percent) from the field in the second half to Eastern Illinois' (2-11, 1-6) 14-of-25 (56 percent) performance. Hopkins was the only player scoring in double figures for Murray. Shawn Witherspoon had 11 rebounds. Mike Robinson led Eastern Illinois with 18 points, and Josh Gomes scored 13.
